org.jconfigurations.converters

Interface MapConfigurationConverter<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    V -
    All Superinterfaces:
    ConfigurationConverter<Map<K,V>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseMapConfigurationConverter, HashMapConfigurationConverter, NoMapConfigurationConverter

    public interface MapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
extends ConfigurationConverter<Map<K,V>>
    MapConfigurationConverters are used by configurators to convert a configuration value into an instance of a Map of types K and V. Default implementations for Map and HashMap are already provided. Users may opt to implement their own converters and specify those via MapConfiguration.converter(). The MapFieldConverterFunction requires that implementations provide an accessible constructor that accepts four arguments:
    1. the keyConverter
    2. the valueConverter
    3. the entryDelimiter
    4. the keyValueSeparator
    MapConfigurationConverters only act upon fields marked with @MapConfiguration.
    Author:
    George Aristy
